"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrew Nembhard and Kelly Olynyk were among the 11 NBA players chosen, as Olynyk was elected the team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s captain.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 339, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Nembhard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Nembhard\"}, {\"begin\": 365, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olynyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\"}, {\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.666476043382097e-37, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olynyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Olynyk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Leading our senior men's national team into the Paris 2024 Olympic Games is an incredible honor,\\\" Olynyk said ina release from the Canadian national team.\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.149068085742371e-20, \"text\": \"Canadian national team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Since I began playing basketball, my dream has always been to represent Canada at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 683, \"end\": 689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9306502344782788, \"rank\": 0.07451681278585583, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year's third-place finish at the FIBA World Cup was an important step, proving that we belong among the world's best teams.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it also showed us that we still have work to do as we pursue our ultimate goal of winning gold in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999993436447192, \"rank\": 6.563555107624574e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olynyk, coming off his 11th NBA season, has played 756 games and posts career averages of 10.3 points, 5.2 rebounds and 2.4 assists.\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 33-year-old signed an extension with the Toronto Raptors in March after being traded from the Utah Jazz.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto_Raptors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.807551864570895e-68, \"text\": \"Toronto Raptors\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto_Raptors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto_Raptors\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olynyk has been a member of Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s senior men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s national team since 2010, when he made his debut at the FIBA World Championship at just 19 years old.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last summer against the Americans, he finished with 11 points in as many minutes while shooting 4-of-6 from the field in the 127-118 win.\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cKelly\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s had an incredible career,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Mark Few said during a press conference in June.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Few\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Few\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Few\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Few\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s done what he does best, man.\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just a really, really smart, tough, really good basketball player and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s why he fits in great everywhere.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Nembhard\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic debut comes after a breakout season as a second-year pro with the Indiana Pacers.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1830, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7351657037325825e-66, \"text\": \"Indiana Pacers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 6-foot-5 guard helped guide Indiana to the Eastern Conference Finals with big-time performances against the New York Knicks in the second round of the playoffs; a 30-foot jumper to seal the deal in Game 3, followed by a 20-point outing in Game 7 days later.\\u00c2  Nembhard averaged 14.9 points and 5.5 assists while posting a true shooting percentage of 65.4% across 17 postseason games.\\u00c2  Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Team Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s final roster: Nickeil Alexander-Walker (Minnesota Timberwolves), RJ Barrett (Toronto Raptors), Khem Birch (formerly of the Toronto Raptors), Dillon Brooks (Houston Rockets), Lugentz Dort (Oklahoma City Thunder), Melvin Ejim (brother of Gonzaga women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball standout Yvonne Ejim), Shai Gilgeous-Alexander (Oklahoma City Thunder), Trey Lyles (Sacramento Kings), Jamal Murray (Denver Nuggets), Dwight Powell (Dallas Mavericks), Olynyk and Nembhard.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\", \"score\": 0.9999998787043369, \"rank\": 1.2129553292563967e-07, \"text\": \"Indiana\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indiana_Pacers\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_playoffs\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.51888942186491e-11, \"text\": \"Eastern Conference Finals\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_playoffs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_playoffs\"}, {\"begin\": 1958, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Knicks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4731415515273463e-64, \"text\": \"New York Knicks\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Knicks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http:/